description: SpaceX launched its fifth test flight of its Starship rocket on Sunday and made a dramatic first catch of the rocket’s more than 20-story tall booster. It comes as SpaceX makes a big push to send people to the moon and Mars in the coming years. NBC News' Steve Patterson has the latest, and what it means for the future of space travel.
title: SpaceX catches Starship rocket booster in historic test launch

description: More than 60 people have been injured according to Israeli rescue services, due to a Hezbollah drone attack in northern Israel. NBC News' Matt Bradley reports on how the U.S. is stepping in to aid the Israelis by deploying the THAAD anti-missile system.
title: More than 60 hurt in Hezbollah drone attack in Israel

description: Gen. Mark Milley called Donald Trump a “fascist,” according to Bob Woodward’s new book. During an interview with Meet the Press, former Rep. Liz Cheney says she has “no reason to disagree with that assessment.”
title: Liz Cheney: ‘No reason to disagree’ with Gen. Mark Milley allegedly calling Trump ‘fascist’

description: During an exclusive interview with Meet the Press, former Rep. Liz Cheney says she is a “conservative” but does not consider herself to be “a member of Donald Trump’s Republican Party.”
title: Liz Cheney says she is not a 'member of Donald Trump's Republican Party'

description: Kamala Harris and Donald Trump are deadlocked in the latest NBC News poll, with Trump bolstered by favorable views of his presidency and Harris by concerns about abortion. NBC News National Political Correspondent Steve Kornacki joins Meet the Press to go through the numbers.
title: Donald Trump pulls even with Kamala Harris in NBC News poll, Steve Kornacki explains

description: Four days after Hurricane Milton roared onto the west coast of Florida, analysts estimate well-over $100 billion of damage. The cost of cleanup, rebuilding and insurance in a coastal hurricane zone have become prohibitive to some residents who are deciding they can no longer afford to live in paradise. NBC’s Stephanie Gosk reports in this week’s Sunday Focus.
title: Hurricanes spark housing disparity amid rising cost of recovery

description: A free family planning center in Twin Falls, Idaho, asks its visitors for sensitive, private information, including nonmedical questions about religion and financial status, according to documents obtained by NBC News.
title: Crisis pregnancy center's forms give rare insight into anti-abortion practices

description: For David Tasker, an 18-year-old construction worker in Pennsylvania, his top financial priorities are having enough money for gas, dining out and spending on his girlfriend while living at home with his parents.
title: Young men’s economic prospects are shifting, along with their politics
